org.jetbrains.jetCheck

Class PropertyChecker

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jetbrains.jetCheck.PropertyChecker

  • public class PropertyChecker
extends Object
    An entry point to property-based testing. The main usage pattern: PropertyChecker.forAll(generator, property).

      • forAll

        public static <T> void forAll(Generator<T> generator,
                              @NotNull
                              Predicate<T> property)
        Checks that the given property returns true and doesn't throw exceptions by running the generator and the property on random data repeatedly for some number of times. To customize the settings, invoke customized() first.

      • checkScenarios

        public static void checkScenarios(@NotNull
                                  Supplier<? extends ImperativeCommand> command)
        Performs a check that the scenarios generated by the given command are successful. Default PropertyChecker settings are used. To customize the settings, invoke customized() first.
        Parameters:
        command - a supplier for a top-level command. This supplier should not have any side effects.

      • customized

        public static PropertyChecker.Parameters customized()
        Returns:
        a "parameters" object that where some checker settings can be changed
